  h2 How long does a Kessler Cascade take?
  p While the 2013 film #[a(href="https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1454468/" target="_blank" rel="noopener") Gravity] portrays a Kessler cascade unfolding over a matter of hours, a real cascade would likely take place over a time on the order of years or decades.
  p This has good and bad implications.
  p On the plus side, we should be able to take action even during the actual cascade. On the other hand, we might not be able to tell that a cascade is happening for years, until it's too far to stop.

